quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  25,21,"And those who do not expect to meet Us said, “If only the angels were sent down to us or we could see our Lord.” They have acted arrogantly regarding themselves and have become excessively defiant."
  25,22,"On the day when they see the angels—no glad tidings for the criminals on that day, and they{1}say, “an insurmountable separator{2}.”",footnotes:1:The angels.From bliss.
  25,23,"And We proceeded{1}to the work they had done and turned them into scattered dust.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  25,24,"The fellows of the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>on that day have a better residence and are more fairly accommodated."
  25,25,"And it is the day when the sky is cleft with clouds and <span class=""h"">the angels were</span><a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a><span class=""h"">sent down<sup foot_note=""80696"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>in streams."
  25,26,"Dominion on that day belongs to the All-Merciful, and it has been a difficult day for the deniers."
  25,27,"And it is the day when the unjust bites his hands, saying, “If only I had followed the way with the Messenger."
  25,28,"Woe to me! I wish I had not taken so-and-so for a close friend;"
  25,29,"he definitely made me stray away from the Reminder after it had come to me.” And Satan has always been a betrayer of man.”"
  25,30,"And the Messenger said<a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>, “O My Lord, my people have dealt with this Recital{1}by deserting it.”",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’an which means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  25,31,"Likewise, to every prophet We assigned enemies from among the criminals. But sufficient is your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord as a Guide and Supporter."
  25,32,"And those who denied said, “If only the Recital<a class=""sup""><sup>e </sup></a>had been sent down upon him as one complete whole!” Yet<i class=""s"">(it is sent in this way) </i>in order to strengthen your heart thereby, and We<i class=""s"">(revealed it to be) </i>chanted slowly and distinctly."
